  "prompt": "What are the new features in iPhone 7?",
  "response": "The iPhone 7, released in September 2016, introduced several new features and improvements over its predecessors. Here are some of the key features:\n\n1. **Improved Camera System**: \n   - The iPhone 7 features a 12-megapixel rear camera with a larger f/1.8 aperture and optical image stabilization, which improves low-light performance and overall image quality.\n   - The front camera was upgraded to a 7-megapixel sensor, allowing for better selfies and FaceTime calls.\n\n2. **Performance Enhancements**: \n   - It is powered by the A10 Fusion chip, Apple\u2019s first quad-core processor, which has two high-performance cores and two energy-efficient cores, providing a significant boost in speed and efficiency.\n\n3. **Display Improvements**:\n   - The 4.7-inch Retina HD display offers a wider color gamut and greater brightness, enhancing the visual experience.\n\n4. **Stereo Speakers**:\n   - The iPhone 7 features stereo speakers, one at the bottom and another at the top, providing a better audio experience.\n\n5. **No Headphone Jack**:\n   - Apple removed the 3.5mm headphone jack, introducing the use of Lightning port headphones and encouraging wireless audio solutions like AirPods.\n\n6. **Water and Dust Resistance**:\n   - It comes with an IP67 rating, meaning it's resistant to splashes, dust, and can even be submerged in water up to 1 meter for 30 minutes.\n\n7. **Home Button Redesign**:\n   - The physical Home button was replaced with a solid-state button that uses haptic feedback to simulate a button press, powered by the Taptic Engine.\n\n8. **New Color Options**:\n   - The iPhone 7 introduced new finishes, including Jet Black and Black, alongside existing options like Gold, Silver, and Rose Gold.\n\nThese features marked a significant evolution from the previous iPhone models, offering improvements in performance, functionality, and design.",
